@Override
public FailureAnalysis analyze(Throwable failure) {
    T cause = findCause(failure, getCauseType());   // <-- traverses cause chain
    return (cause != null) ? analyze(failure, cause) : null;
}

protected final <E extends Throwable> E findCause(Throwable failure, Class<E> type) {
    while (failure != null) {                        // <-- iterates through cause chain
        if (type.isInstance(failure)) {
            return (E) failure;
        }
        failure = failure.getCause();                // <-- walks down to cause
    }
    return null;
}
```

The `findCause()` method walks the entire cause chain (`failure`, `failure.getCause()`, `failure.getCause().getCause()`, etc.) and returns the **first** exception that matches type `T`.

